: a Dormouse was sitting
  between them, fast asleep, and the other two were
  using it as a cushion, resting their elbows on it,
  and talking over its head. 'Very uncomfortable for
  the Dormouse,' thought Alice; 'only, as it's asleep, I
  suppose it doesn't mind.'

  The table was a large one, but the three were all
  sitting in a corner together, with their elbows on
  the table, and their heads bent forward, talking
  together in a whisper; and as Alice came out of the
  wood into the sunshine, she could hear them
  perfectly well.

  'Where's the Duchess?' said Alice. 'And the baby?'

  The Hatter looked at her very sadly, and then
  began counting on his fingers. 'One, two, three,' he
  said. 'Two hours for dinner,' he added in
